{"award_age":62.0,"bio_image":"full\/5a5f820254dac907049ea7f3d4818a9b355728ed.jpg","category":"Literature","country":"Saint Lucia","date_of_birth":"1930-01-23T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/a\/af\/Derek_Walcott.jpg\/220px-Derek_Walcott.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Derek_Walcott","mini_bio":"<p><b>Derek Alton Walcott<\/b>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Officer_of_the_Order_of_the_British_Empire\" title=\"Officer of the Order of the British Empire\" class=\"mw-redirect\">OBE<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_the_Caribbean_Community\" title=\"Order of the Caribbean Community\">OCC<\/a> (born 23 January 1930) is a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Saint_Lucia\" title=\"Saint Lucia\">Saint Lucian<\/a> poet and playwright. He received the 1992 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Literature\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Literature\">Nobel Prize in Literature<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Derek_Walcott#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He is currently Professor of Poetry at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Essex\" title=\"University of Essex\">University of Essex<\/a>. His works include the Homeric epic poem <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Omeros\" title=\"Omeros\">Omeros<\/a><\/i> (1990), which many critics view \"as Walcott's major achievement.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-poetryfoundation.org_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Derek_Walcott#cite_note-poetryfoundation.org-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Poetry_Found_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Derek_Walcott#cite_note-Poetry_Found-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In addition to having won the Nobel, Walcott has won many literary awards over the course of his career, including an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Obie_Award\" title=\"Obie Award\">Obie Award<\/a> in 1971 for his play <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dream_on_Monkey_Mountain\" title=\"Dream on Monkey Mountain\">Dream on Monkey Mountain<\/a><\/i>, a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/MacArthur_Foundation\" title=\"MacArthur Foundation\" class=\"mw-redirect\">MacArthur Foundation<\/a> \"genius\" award, a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Royal_Society_of_Literature\" title=\"Royal Society of Literature\">Royal Society of Literature<\/a> Award, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Queen%27s_Gold_Medal_for_Poetry\" title=\"Queen's Gold Medal for Poetry\">Queen's Medal for Poetry<\/a>, the inaugural <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/OCM_Bocas_Prize_for_Caribbean_Literature\" title=\"OCM Bocas Prize for Caribbean Literature\">OCM Bocas Prize for Caribbean Literature<\/a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Derek_Walcott#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and the 2011 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/T._S._Eliot_Prize\" title=\"T. S. Eliot Prize\">T. S. Eliot Prize<\/a> for his book of poetry <i>White Egrets<\/i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Eliot_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Derek_Walcott#cite_note-Eliot-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Derek Walcott","place_of_birth":"Castries ,  Saint Lucia","place_of_death":null,"text":"Derek Walcott , Literature, 1992","year":1992.0}